{"title_page": "Kelly Keisling", "text_new": "{{Infobox state representative\n|name        = Kelly Keisling\n|image       = \n|state_house = Tennessee\n|district    = 38th<ref name=\"TL\">{{cite web |url= http://www.capitol.tn.gov/house/members/h38.html |title= Rep. Kelly Keisling |publisher= [[Tennessee General Assembly]] |location= [[Nashville, Tennessee]] |accessdate= March 17, 2014}}</ref>\n|term_start  = January 2011\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Leslie Winningham]]\n|successor   = Incumbent\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1951|3|16}}\n|birth_place = [[Albany, Kentucky]]\n|death_date  =\n|death_place =\n|nationality = [[United States|American]]\n|party       = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|spouse      = Janet Keisling\n|children    = Jamie Edwards, Karissa Jones and John Keisling\n|residence   = [[Byrdstown, Tennessee]]\n|alma_mater  = [[Belmont University]]\n|profession  = Insurance\n|religion    = Southern Baptist\n|website     = kellykeislingtn.com\n}}\n\nA Kentuckian by birth, but raised in Tennessee and educated in our state\u2019s public school system, '''State Representative Kelly Keisling''' has served the 38th House District in the Tennessee General Assembly since 2010. Currently, he serves as chairman of the State Committee along with being a member of the following committees:\u200b\u200b Departments & Agencies Subcommittee, Public Service & Employees Subcommittee, Corrections Subcommittee, Calendar & Rules Committee, Agriculture and Natural Resources Committee, Transportation Committee, and Infrastructure Committee. \n \nOver the years of his service, he has been recognized as Legislator of the Year by Upper Cumberland Development District, East Tennessee Development District, Rural Health Association of Tennessee, Upper Cumberland EMS Directors Association, Tennessee Federation for the Aging\u200b , County Officials Association of Tennessee, and Tennessee Renewable Energy Council. \n\nIn addition to his legislative duties, he serves on the Board of Directors of the Children\u2019s Center of the Cumberlands; President, Keisling Insurance; member of the following Chamber of Commerce\u2019s: Macon, Clay, Pickett, Fentress and Scott Counties; member, Tennessee State Employees Association.\n \nRepresentative Keisling and wife, Janet, are the proud parents of three adult children, seven wonderful grandchildren, and two beautiful great-grandchildren. They reside in Byrdstown and are members of Etter Baptist Church.\n\n\n\n\n==Education==\nKeisling attended [[Belmont University]].\n\n==Elections==\n*2012 Keisling was unopposed for the August 2, 2012 Republican Primary, winning with 4,575 votes,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-08/RepPrimaryPrecinctTotals.pdf |title= State of Tennessee August 2, 2012 Republican Primary |publisher= [[Tennessee Secretary of State]] |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 156 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140313183820/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-08/RepPrimaryPrecinctTotals.pdf |archive-date= March 13, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref> and won the November 6, 2012 General election with 14,190 votes (71.8%) against [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee David Harper.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-11/TNHousePrecinctTotals.pdf |title= State of Tennessee November 6, 2012 General Election |publisher= Tennessee Secretary of State |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 39 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140313183815/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-11/TNHousePrecinctTotals.pdf |archive-date= March 13, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n*2010 To challenge District 38 incumbent Democratic Representative [[Leslie Winningham]], Keisling was unopposed for the August 5, 2010 Republican Primary, winning with 5,537 votes,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-08/RepTNHousePrecinct.pdf |title= State of Tennessee August 5, 2010 Republican Primary |publisher= Tennessee Secretary of State |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 31 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140314000509/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-08/RepTNHousePrecinct.pdf |archive-date= March 14, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref> and won the November 2, 2010 General election with 7,965 votes (56.5%) against Representative Winningham.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-11/TNHPrecinct.pdf |title= State of Tennessee November 2, 2010 State General |publisher= Tennessee Secretary of State |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 31 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140313223338/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-11/TNHPrecinct.pdf |archive-date= March 13, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.capitol.tn.gov/house/members/h38.html Official page] at the [[Tennessee General Assembly]]\n*{{CongLinks | congbio = | votesmart = 125428 | fec = | congress = }}\n*[http://ballotpedia.org/Kelly_Keisling Kelly Keisling] at [[Ballotpedia]]\n*[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/uniquecandidate.phtml?uc=143647 Kelly T. Keisling] at the National Institute on Money in State Politics\n*[http://www.kellykeislingtn.com Official Campaign Website] via [[State Representative Kelly Keisling ]]\n\n{{Tennessee House of Representatives |state= collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Keisling, Kelly}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belmont University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Tennessee House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:People from Albany, Kentucky]]\n[[Category:People from Pickett County, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Republicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n\n\n{{Tennessee-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox state representative\n|name        = Kelly Keisling\n|image       = \n|state_house = Tennessee\n|district    = 38th<ref name=\"TL\">{{cite web |url= http://www.capitol.tn.gov/house/members/h38.html |title= Rep. Kelly Keisling |publisher= [[Tennessee General Assembly]] |location= [[Nashville, Tennessee]] |accessdate= March 17, 2014}}</ref>\n|term_start  = January 2011\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Leslie Winningham]]\n|successor   = Incumbent\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1951|3|16}}\n|birth_place = [[Albany, Kentucky]]\n|death_date  =\n|death_place =\n|nationality = [[United States|American]]\n|party       = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|spouse      = Janet Keisling\n|children    = Jamie Edwards, Karissa Jones and John Keisling\n|residence   = [[Byrdstown, Tennessee]]\n|alma_mater  = [[Belmont University]]\n|profession  = Insurance\n|religion    = Southern Baptist\n|website     = kellykeislingtn.com\n}}\n\n'''Kelly T. Keisling''', a Kentuckian by birth, but raised in Tennessee and educated in our state\u2019s public school system, Representative Keisling has served the 38th House District in the Tennessee General Assembly since 2010. Currently, he serves as chairman of the State Committee along with being a member of the following committees:\u200b\u200b Departments & Agencies Subcommittee, Public Service & Employees Subcommittee, Corrections Subcommittee, Calendar & Rules Committee, Agriculture and Natural Resources Committee, Transportation Committee, and Infrastructure Committee. \n \nOver the years of his service, he has been recognized as Legislator of the Year by Upper Cumberland Development District, East Tennessee Development District, Rural Health Association of Tennessee, Upper Cumberland EMS Directors Association, Tennessee Federation for the Aging\u200b , County Officials Association of Tennessee, and Tennessee Renewable Energy Council. \n\nIn addition to his legislative duties, he serves on the Board of Directors of the Children\u2019s Center of the Cumberlands; President, Keisling Insurance; member of the following Chamber of Commerce\u2019s: Macon, Clay, Pickett, Fentress and Scott Counties; member, Tennessee State Employees Association.\n \nRepresentative Keisling and wife, Janet, are the proud parents of three adult children, seven wonderful grandchildren, and two beautiful great-grandchildren. They reside in Byrdstown and are members of Etter Baptist Church.\n\n\n\n\n==Education==\nKeisling attended [[Belmont University]].\n\n==Elections==\n*2012 Keisling was unopposed for the August 2, 2012 Republican Primary, winning with 4,575 votes,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-08/RepPrimaryPrecinctTotals.pdf |title= State of Tennessee August 2, 2012 Republican Primary |publisher= [[Tennessee Secretary of State]] |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 156 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140313183820/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-08/RepPrimaryPrecinctTotals.pdf |archive-date= March 13, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref> and won the November 6, 2012 General election with 14,190 votes (71.8%) against [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee David Harper.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-11/TNHousePrecinctTotals.pdf |title= State of Tennessee November 6, 2012 General Election |publisher= Tennessee Secretary of State |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 39 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140313183815/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2012-11/TNHousePrecinctTotals.pdf |archive-date= March 13, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n*2010 To challenge District 38 incumbent Democratic Representative [[Leslie Winningham]], Keisling was unopposed for the August 5, 2010 Republican Primary, winning with 5,537 votes,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-08/RepTNHousePrecinct.pdf |title= State of Tennessee August 5, 2010 Republican Primary |publisher= Tennessee Secretary of State |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 31 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140314000509/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-08/RepTNHousePrecinct.pdf |archive-date= March 14, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref> and won the November 2, 2010 General election with 7,965 votes (56.5%) against Representative Winningham.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-11/TNHPrecinct.pdf |title= State of Tennessee November 2, 2010 State General |publisher= Tennessee Secretary of State |location= Nashville, Tennessee |page= 31 |accessdate= March 17, 2014 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140313223338/http://tennessee.gov/sos/election/results/2010-11/TNHPrecinct.pdf |archive-date= March 13, 2014 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.capitol.tn.gov/house/members/h38.html Official page] at the [[Tennessee General Assembly]]\n*{{CongLinks | congbio = | votesmart = 125428 | fec = | congress = }}\n*[http://ballotpedia.org/Kelly_Keisling Kelly Keisling] at [[Ballotpedia]]\n*[http://www.followthemoney.org/database/uniquecandidate.phtml?uc=143647 Kelly T. Keisling] at the National Institute on Money in State Politics\n*[http://www.kellykeislingtn.com Official Campaign Website] via [[State Representative Kelly Keisling ]]\n\n{{Tennessee House of Representatives |state= collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Keisling, Kelly}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belmont University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the Tennessee House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:People from Albany, Kentucky]]\n[[Category:People from Pickett County, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Tennessee Republicans]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n\n\n{{Tennessee-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Zdstephens21", "label": "safe", "comment": "bolded name", "url_page": "//en.wi